#read match data
matches = readRDS("df9b1196-e3cf-4cc7-9159-f236fe738215_matches.rds")

# remove duplicate rows
matches = matches[!duplicated(matches)]

#manipulate score to break home score from away score
matches[,c('score_home', 'score_away') := tstrsplit(score,':')]

#remove unnecessary columns
matches = matches[,c("matchId", "date", "score_home", "score_away")]

#calculate real match scores
matches[,c('result') := ifelse(as.numeric(score_away) + as.numeric(score_home) > 2.5, "over", "under")]

matches = matches[result=="under" | result=="over"]

# Create Bookmaker Plot Function -------------------------------------------------------
plotFunction = function(df) {
  
  df = df[order(matchId, oddtype, date)]
  
  # initial odds data, get the first ou result of the same matchId
  df_initial = df[, list(initial_odd = odd[1]), by = list(matchId, oddtype)]
  df_final = df[, list(final_odd = odd[.N]), by = list(matchId, oddtype)]
  
  # change the order the odds data based on ou columns
  df_initial = dcast(df_initial, matchId ~ oddtype, value.var = 'initial_odd')
  df_final = dcast(df_final, matchId ~ oddtype, value.var = 'final_odd')
  
  #calculate and normalize probabilities
  df_initial = df_initial[, over_prob := (1/over)/(1/over+1/under)]
  df_initial = df_initial[, under_prob := (1/under)/(1/over+1/under)]
  df_final = df_final[, over_prob := (1/over)/(1/over+1/under)]
  df_final = df_final[, under_prob := (1/under)/(1/over+1/under)]
  
  #merge results and odds
  df_initial_with_results = merge(df_initial, matches[,list(matchId, result)], by=c('matchId')) 
  df_final_with_results = merge(df_final, matches[,list(matchId, result)], by=c('matchId')) 
  
  cutpoints = seq(0, 1, 0.05)
  
  df_initial_with_results = df_initial_with_results[, discrete_over := cut(over_prob, cutpoints)]
  df_final_with_results = df_final_with_results[, discrete_over := cut(over_prob, cutpoints)]
  
  summary_initial = df_initial_with_results[,list(overs = sum(result == 'over'), .N, avg_prob = mean(over_prob)), 
                                            by = list(discrete_over)]
  summary_final = df_final_with_results[,list(overs = sum(result == 'over'), .N, avg_prob = mean(over_prob)), 
                                        by = list(discrete_over)]
  
  summary_initial[, ratio := overs / N]
  summary_final[, ratio := overs / N]
  
  par(mfrow = c(1,2))
  
  plot(summary_initial[,list(ratio, avg_prob)], cex=0.3, xlab = "Fraction of games finished over",
       ylab = "Probability Average", main="Initial Odds")
  abline(0,1,col='red')
  lines(lowess(summary_initial$ratio, summary_initial$avg_prob), col="blue", lwd=1)
  
  plot(summary_final[,list(ratio, avg_prob)], cex=0.3, xlab = "Fraction of games finished over",
       ylab = "Probability Average", main="Final Odds")
  abline(0,1,col='red')
  lines(lowess(summary_final$ratio, summary_final$avg_prob), col="blue", lwd=1)
}

# Create year plot function for part b --------
plotByYearFunction = function(df, year1, year2) {
  
  par(mfrow=c(1,2))
  df_year1 = df[date == year1]
  
  plot(df_year1[,list(ratio, avg_prob)], cex=0.3, xlab = "Fraction of games finished over",
       ylab = "Probability Average", main=toString(year1))
  abline(0,1,col='red')
  lines(lowess(df_year1$ratio, df_year1$avg_prob), col="blue", lwd=1)
  
  df_year2 = df[date == year2]
  plot(df_year2[,list(ratio, avg_prob)], cex=0.3, xlab = "Fraction of games finished over",
       ylab = "Probability Average", main=toString(year2))
  abline(0,1,col='red')
  lines(lowess(df_year2$ratio, df_year2$avg_prob), col="blue", lwd=1)
}
